Definition.WordDefinition: Biochemistry \Bi`o*chem"is*try\, n. [Gr. bi`os life + E. chemistry.] (Biol.) The chemistry of living organisms; the chemistry of the processes incidental to, and characteristic of, life. [1913 Webster]
biochemistry n : the organic chemistry of compounds and processes occuring in organisms; the effort to understand biology within the context of chemistry
